Wash and dry all produce. Preheat the oven to 450 degrees. Cut the @sweet potatoes{12%ounce} into sticks (like French fries), keeping the skin on. Halve the @grape tomatoes{4%ounce}. Chop the @baby gem lettuce{1}(chopped) into 1-inch pieces. Mince the @garlic{2%cloves}(minced). Halve the @lemon{1}(halved).

Toss the sweet potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp} and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Place in the oven for about ~{25%minutes}, tossing halfway through cooking, until crispy and golden brown.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp} in a large #pan{} over medium heat. Add the garlic and cook for ~{30%seconds}, or until fragrant. Remove the pan from the heat and toss in the @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup} and @chili powder{1%tsp}. Season with @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}.

Place the @chicken breasts{12%ounce} onto a lightly oiled baking sheet and coat each with a large dollop of @sour cream{4%tbsp}. Then season with @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Press the panko mixture onto the tops of each chicken breast to adhere. Place them on a baking sheet in the oven for ~{15-20%minutes}, until the chicken is just cooked through.

When the chicken is almost ready, toss the chopped lettuce and tomatoes in a large #bowl{} with a squeeze of lemon juice and a large drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp}. Season to taste with @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}.

Finish and plate: Serve the crispy spiced chicken with the sweet potato fries and garden salad alongside. Enjoy!